## Development Commands

```bash
# Full stack
docker compose up -d                  # Start all containers
docker compose down                   # Stop all containers
docker compose logs -f backend        # Backend logs
docker compose logs -f frontend       # Frontend logs

# Backend (Django)
docker compose exec backend python manage.py migrate
docker compose exec backend python manage.py makemigrations
docker compose exec backend python manage.py createsuperuser
docker compose exec backend pytest
docker compose exec backend pytest --cov=apps

# GraphQL schema export
docker compose exec backend python manage.py export_schema --path schema.graphql

# Frontend (Next.js)
docker compose exec frontend npm run dev
docker compose exec frontend npm run build
docker compose exec frontend npm run codegen        # Generate types from schema
docker compose exec frontend npm run codegen:watch  # Watch mode
docker compose exec frontend npm test
docker compose exec frontend npm run lint
```

---

## GraphQL API

### Endpoint
- **URL:** `http://localhost:8000/graphql/`
- **Method:** POST (queries/mutations), GET (playground in dev)

### Authentication
- JWT tokens via `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header

### Example Query
```graphql
query GetCurrentUser {
  me {
    id
    email
    firstName
    lastName
  }
}
```

### Example Mutation
```graphql
mutation Login($email: String!, $password: String!) {
  tokenAuth(email: $email, password: $password) {
    token
    refreshToken
  }
}
```

---

## Code Conventions

### Backend (Django / Strawberry)
- Business logic lives in **Services**, not resolvers — keep resolvers thin
- **No traditional views** — all data exposed via GraphQL (exceptions: webhooks, health checks)
- **Class-Based Views (CBVs)** when views are required
- **Strict type hints** required on all Python code

```python
import strawberry
from typing import Optional

@strawberry.type
class UserType:
    id: strawberry.ID
    email: str
    first_name: str
    last_name: str

    @strawberry.field
    def full_name(self) -> str:
        return f"{self.first_name} {self.last_name}"
```

### Frontend (Next.js / TypeScript)
- **Functional components only** with TypeScript interfaces
- Use **Next.js App Router** conventions (Server Components by default, `"use client"` only when needed)
- Use generated Apollo hooks from `src/graphql/generated/`
- Tailwind CSS v4 utilities for all styling — no hardcoded colours

